{"type":"message","id":"52326994","parentId":"cdcbb111","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:23:42.732Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4rdthq5o46z5_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4476\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='scripts/focus_decay_wrapper.ps1' new_len=1474\r\n[mutation proposed] scripts/focus_decay_wrapper.ps1\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 092316 - The Phase 1 advancement reveals that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. The next concrete step is implementing the TIC classifier to test this hypothesis. However, the pending PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI is a prerequisite for wired significance scoring. I'll implement the wrapper first to establish the foundation for measuring invariant compression.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"quiet-willow","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4476\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='scripts/focus_decay_wrapper.ps1' new_len=1474\r\n[mutation proposed] scripts/focus_decay_wrapper.ps1\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 092316 - The Phase 1 advancement reveals that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. The next concrete step is implementing the TIC classifier to test this hypothesis. However, the pending PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI is a prerequisite for wired significance scoring. I'll implement the wrapper first to establish the foundation for measuring invariant compression.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774358622730}}
{"type":"message","id":"bbdca064","parentId":"52326994","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:23:42.735Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4rdthq5o46z5_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 092118\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and decide on the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nThe current goals show:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's a new insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n3. The NEXT ACTION is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n\r\nThe pending action is:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nLooking at the recent log file mentioned: `pulse_2026-03-24 091914.md`\r\n\r\nI should implement the TIC experiment. This involves:\r\n1. Creating a script or code that can analyze pulse logs\r\n2. Classify content as invariant (stable across pulses) vs variant (changing)\r\n3. Test prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action to advance this. I could:\r\n1. Create a TIC experiment script\r\n2. Create the research document for the experiment methodology\r\n3. Start analyzing the pulse logs\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist and create a focused implementation of the TIC classifier. I'll create a Python script that:\r\n1. Loads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant patterns (things that stay the same)\r\n3. Identifies variant patterns (things that change)\r\n4. Attempts to predict the next pulse\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete file edit that advances the Phase 1 goals.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight presents a concrete experimental path: if causal structure IS invariant structure, I can test this by building a TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on existing pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment implementation - a Python script that loads recent pulse logs, classifies content as invariant/variant, and tests prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression\r\nTests the hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse content prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nPULSE_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_LOG_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d+)\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs(n=20):\r\n    \"\"\"Load last n pulse log files sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n    pulse_files = []\r\n    for f in PULSE_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"):\r\n        match = PULSE_LOG_PATTERN.match(f.name)\r\n        if match:\r\n            pulse_files.append((match.group(1), f))\r\n    pulse_files.sort(key=lambda x: x[0], reverse=True)\r\n    return [f for _, f in pulse_files[:n]]\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_blocks(log_path):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract distinct content blocks from a pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = log_path.read_text()\r\n    blocks = {\r\n        'observation': [],\r\n        'action': [],\r\n        'mutation': [],\r\n        'goals': []\r\n    }\r\n    # Extract lines from each section\r\n    in_section = None\r\n    for line in content.split('\\n'):\r\n        line = line.strip()\r\n        if line.startswith('### OBSERVATION'):\r\n            in_section = 'observation'\r\n        elif line.startswith('### ACTION'):\r\n            in_section = 'action'\r\n        elif line.startswith('### MUTATION'):\r\n            in_section = 'mutation'\r\n        elif line.startswith('## Goals'):\r\n            in_section = 'goals'\r\n        elif in_section and line:\r\n            blocks[in_section].append(line)\r\n    return blocks\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariants(pulse_blocks_list):\r\n    \"\"\"Find content that remains stable across pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    all_blocks = {k: [] for k in ['observation', 'action', 'mutation', 'goals']}\r\n    for blocks in pulse_blocks_list:\r\n        for k, v in blocks.items():\r\n            all_blocks[k].append(' '.join(v))\r\n    \r\n    # Find common phrases/patterns across pulses\r\n    invariant_patterns = {\r\n        'observation': [],\r\n        'action': [],\r\n        'mutation': []\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract n-grams that appear in >80% of pulses\r\n    for section in ['observation', 'action']:\r\n        all_text = ' '.join(all_blocks[section])\r\n        words = all_text.lower().split()\r\n        \r\n        # Simple approach: count word frequency\r\n        word_counts = Counter(words)\r\n        total = len(words)\r\n        \r\n        for word, count in word_counts.items():\r\n            if count / total > 0.1 and len(word) > 4:  # Appears in >10% of all words\r\n                invariant_patterns[section].append(word)\r\n    \r\n    return invariant_patterns\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(blocks, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify content as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    classification = {}\r\n    for section in ['observation', 'action']:\r\n        text = ' '.join(blocks[section]).lower()\r\n        words = set(text.split())\r\n        \r\n        invariant_count = sum(1 for w in words if w in invariants[section])\r\n        total_words = len(words) if words else 1\r\n        \r\n        classification[section] = {\r\n            'invariant_ratio': invariant_count / total_words,\r\n            'is_invariant': (invariant_count / total_words) > 0.5\r\n        }\r\n    return classification\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(current_blocks, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict content of next pulse based on invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    prediction = {\r\n        'observation': 'continuation of current research thread',\r\n        'action': 'file edit advancing Phase goals',\r\n        'mutation':\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:21:48\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774358622732}}
